var DYK_FACTS = ["Corte Bella has recorded 1,794 closed sales since 2010 \u2014 averaging 105 sales per year.","Corte Bella was Del Webb's first foray into the country club format \u2014 designed to give buyers the amenity package of a Del Webb community in a smaller, more intimate setting.","All 1,650 homes in Corte Bella were built between 2003 and 2007 by Del Webb (Pulte Homes). Buildout was complete in October 2007.","Corte Bella's championship 18-hole golf course was designed by Greg Nash and stretches 7,011 yards from the championship tees.","The 45+ age restriction (instead of the typical 55+) makes Corte Bella distinct from neighboring Sun City West and Sun City Grand.","Corte Bella has its own master HOA at approximately $407/quarter \u2014 separate from Sun City West's $598/person rec card. Residents of one community do NOT have access to the other's amenities.","Architectural style at Corte Bella is Santa Barbara / Mediterranean: stucco walls, tile roofs, archways, courtyards, and Italian Cypress trees lining the streets.","The most-traded plan in Corte Bella's resale history is the Arcada, with 137 closed sales since 2010.","The Corte Bella clubhouse complex is 20,000 sq ft total: 9,000 sq ft Social Hall plus an 11,000 sq ft fitness center and spa.","The on-site restaurant is the Corte Bella Grille, located in the golf clubhouse with views over the course and surrounding mountains. It's open to both residents and the public."];
